---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<LegalLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="How TrailNestCo researches, tests, writes, and publishes product guides and reviews." path="/editorial-policy" updated="June 1, 2026">
  <p>
    This policy explains how {SITE.name} selects, tests, and publishes the gear guides and reviews on this
    site. It applies to every article published under our byline, regardless of whether it includes
    affiliate links.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
  <p>
    Our editorial team has full and final authority over which products are covered, how they are scored,
    and what is published. Affiliate partners, brands, and advertisers have no influence over our rankings,
    ratings, or recommendations. We do not accept payment in exchange for positive coverage, and we do not
    allow brands to review or approve articles before publication.
  </p>

  <h2>Our workflow</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Draft</strong> — A staff writer with category expertise researches the product category, tests products hands-on where possible, and writes the initial draft.</li>
    <li><strong>Review</strong> — A senior editor checks the draft for factual accuracy, verifies specifications against manufacturer documentation, and confirms pricing and availability.</li>
    <li><strong>Edited</strong> — The senior editor edits for clarity, structure, and adherence to our style guide.</li>
    <li><strong>Published</strong> — The Editor-in-Chief signs off and the article goes live with full author and reviewer attribution.</li>
    <li><strong>Updated</strong> — Articles are revisited on a regular schedule (or sooner if a product is discontinued or a major price change occurs) and the "last updated" date is revised accordingly.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>How we test</h2>
  <p>
    Where possible, our team purchases or otherwise obtains products for hands-on testing under real-world
    conditions — multi-night camping trips, household use over several weeks, or comparable field testing.
    When hands-on testing isn't feasible for every item in a roundup, we supplement with verified
    manufacturer specifications, owner/expert interviews, and analysis of long-term user feedback. We
    indicate within each article when a product was hands-on tested versus desk-researched.
  </p>

  <h2>Author and reviewer attribution</h2>
  <p>
    Every article displays its writer, expertise tags, and the senior editor who fact-checked it, along
    with publish and last-updated dates. Full bios are available on each <a href="/about">author's page</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>
    If you spot an error, please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.business.editorialEmail}`}>{SITE.business.editorialEmail}</a>.
    We investigate every report and correct verified errors promptly, noting significant corrections in the
    article's update history.
  </p>

  <p>See also our <a href="/fact-checking-policy">Fact-Checking Policy</a> and <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.</p>
</LegalLayout>
